sql:
SELECT videos.video_title, users.user_name
FROM videos
INNER JOIN users ON videos.user_id = users.user_id;

SELECT video_id, video_title
FROM videos
ORDER BY view_count DESC;

SELECT video_id, video_title, SUM(like_count) AS TotalLikes
FROM videos
GROUP BY video_id, video_title;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM videos 
WHERE view_count BETWEEN 1000 AND 5000;

SELECT video_title, video_description, duration
FROM videos
WHERE video_id = '001';

external_knowledge:
- 'certain user' refers to the specific user whose username is 'Your User Name';
- 'popularity' is indicated by the average view count of the videos;
- 'volume of content' refers to the total number of videos;
- 'various categories' means different video categories the user has contributed to.

